A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Lottie Watkins; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Lottie Watkins; and
4 WHEREAS, Lottie Watkins was born on June 4, 1918, in Atlanta, Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, in 1960, she paved the way for Black real estate professionals and home owners
6 with the founding of Lottie Watkins Enterprises, Inc.; and
7 WHEREAS, she selflessly served in the Georgia House of Representatives from 1977 to
8 1980, advocating for economic development, civil rights, social justice, and voter rights; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2023, a marker was installed at the Lottie Watkins building on Ralph David
10 Abernathy Boulevard, in West End, Atlanta, to commemorate her legacy as a trail blazer in
11 real estate, politics, and community development; and
